Really crappy acting, a crappy script, but somehow this is a pretty good storyline that hooks you, and does make you wonder what will happen next.  Will the acting improve? (it does just a tiny bit every episode.), Will the script improve? (Sort of, with increasing attempts at dry humor,)  The premise of the story has just the right mix of plausibility to make you keep staring at your screen, trying to decide if this is worth watching.  It has potential, lots of potential in the way a glass teetering on the edge of a table has potential.  When the acting is this bad and the actors seem like they are reading their lines for maybe only the first time out loud, that's generally all you have; potential.  Oddly, if there is a season 2, I think I want to watch it.  I actually cared what might happen to the characters. These terrible actors somehow grew on me, and I found myself cheering for their careers and willing to go along for the ride.
